Red Pikmin have a sharp, nose-like spine on their face—and they're immune to fire! They're trusty allies you can rely on in any situation.
Blue Pikmin have special gills that let them breathe underwater. Unsurprisingly, they love the water and are excellent swimmers.
Yellow Pikmin have ear-like membranes on the sides of their heads, and they love electricity so much you can sometimes hear them buzzing.
Purple Pikmin are extra large, and they have little hair-like feelers on their heads. They're super strong—but they're also super slow.
White Pikmin have big red eyes compared to their small, nimble bodies. Don't let their size fool you, though; they're poisonous!
Rock Pikmin are as tough as they come. They can break any crystal or glass with ease.
Winged Pikmin have large eyes, a striped belly, and most importantly, wings! They can fly from place to place quickly, but they're not very strong.

In this world, there are small creatures that look a little like animals and a little like plants. We call them Pikmin.

Pick up and hold a Pikmin here to see details
The huge flower you can see in walk view is called a Big Flower.
Pikmin can help this flower grow even bigger by planting flowers around it. What kind of nectar would a blossom like that produce?
The blossoms on Big Flowers are always changing size... Rumor is it that their sizes have to do with the flowers planted nearby. Try planting different sorts of flowers and see what happens!
It looks like Pikmin can grow different colors and types of flowers based on the type of nectar they eat.
Tap on the Nectar to switch to a different type. Try giving your Pikmin different types of nectar and see what happens.
You can now send your Pikmin on challenges!
In the challenge, everyone sends their Pikmin to a single location to work together.
Sending lots of Pikmin, or choosing Pikmin with good friendship levels will help you finish tasks faster and give you a nice reward.
The higher your level, the more Pikmin you will be able to send. Let's work together to send as many Pikmin as we can!
You can now add and change your name. This name will be used to refer to you and will be displayed throughout the game. You can change your name in the settings page.
You can now set your flower planting Privacy Zones from the settings screen!

Privacy zones are areas where flowers won’t be planted when you walk in flower planting mode.
Your privacy zones only apply to you, and won’t affect other users.
If you walk within your privacy zone while planting flowers, flower petals will be consumed over time as usual. The flower planting boost will also be effective.
Make use of privacy zones, and enjoy flower planting with peace of mind!
